---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description="About the Consumer Product Recalls project: a Python data pipeline, a FastAPI service, and this static Astro site."
>
  <div class="max-w-prose">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold sm:text-4xl">About this project</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-muted">
      Consumer product recalls are scattered across five federal agencies, each with its own site,
      format, and quirks. This project unifies them into one searchable, honest, and fast view — and
      doubles as an end-to-end data-engineering portfolio.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl font-bold">How the data flows</h2>
    <ol class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-muted">
      <li>
        <strong class="text-ink">Pipeline.</strong> A Python + dbt pipeline ingests CPSC, FDA, USDA, NHTSA,
        and USCG feeds nightly, conforming them through bronze → silver → gold layers in Postgres, with
        firm resolution and a careful, source-native data contract.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong class="text-ink">API.</strong> A read-only FastAPI service serves the gold tables — entity
        and search endpoints plus pre-aggregated <code>/stats/*</code> for dashboards — with keyset pagination,
        open CORS, and honest, documented caveats.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong class="text-ink">This site.</strong> A static Astro site on Cloudflare Pages. Slow-moving
        aggregates are baked at build time; per-recall browsing and search are fetched live. It never
        touches the database — only the API.
      </li>
    </ol>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl font-bold">Built with</h2>
    <ul class="mt-3 grid grid-cols-2 gap-x-6 gap-y-1 text-sm text-muted sm:grid-cols-3">
      <li>Astro (static)</li>
      <li>React islands</li>
      <li>TanStack Query</li>
      <li>Observable Plot + D3</li>
      <li>Tailwind CSS</li>
      <li>TypeScript (strict)</li>
      <li>OpenAPI-generated client</li>
      <li>Cloudflare Pages</li>
      <li>FastAPI · Postgres · dbt</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-2xl font-bold">Honesty first</h2>
    <p class="mt-1 text-muted">
      The hardest part of unifying five sources is <em>not</em> over-claiming. Classifications, geography,
      lifecycle, and units are kept source-native and clearly captioned. See the
      <a href="/methodology">methodology &amp; caveats</a> and the
      <a href="/api">API reference</a>.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-6 text-sm text-muted">
      Not affiliated with any government agency. Always confirm a recall on the issuing agency's
      official site before acting.
    </p>
  </div>
</Layout>
